		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">I propose to continue my work on quantum gravity by investigating topology changing processes by seeking appropriate instantons.  Topology change will also be studied by using Morse theory and quantum field theory on topology changing backgrounds.  Research on topological geons will continue by me looking at 2+1 gravity as a model amongst other approaches.  I will also study the exciting question of whether D-branes provide a microscopic explanation for black hole entropy as has been claimed.  I will further a proposal that causal sets could be the right description of the underlying discrete substructure of spacetime by investigating several questions.  Some of these questions are kinematical in nature and focus on how and under what conditions a causal set can be well approximated by a Lorentzian manifold.  Other questions are dynamical and centre around the questions of what the correct quantum measure for a causal set is.  Finally I intend to study various history-based approaches to quantum measurement that would be especially applicable to a quantum theory of gravity.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
